   @param {string} [opt.fontFamily]
   @return {string} font string.

renderItem.return.desc:
renderItem should returns graphic element definitions. Each graphic element is an object. See [graphic][0] for detailed info. (But width\height\top\bottom is not supported here) If nothing should be rendered in this data item, just returns nothing. For example: 

    // Returns a rectangular.
    {
        type: 'rect',
        shape: {
            x: x, y: y, width: width, height: height
        },
        style: api.style()
    }


    // Returns a group of elements.
    {
        type: 'group',
        // If diffChildrenByName is set as `true`, `child.name` will be used
        // to diff children, which improves animation transition but degrade
        // performance. The default value is `false`.
        // diffChildrenByName: true,
        children: [{
            type: 'circle',
            shape: {
                cx: cx, cy: cy, r: r
            },
            style: api.style()
        }, {
            type: 'line',
            shape: {
                x1: x1, y1: y1, x2: x2, y2: y2
            },
            style: api.style()
        }]
    }




