renderItem.return_ring.transition.desc:
 Can be a single property name or an array of property names. Enable transition animation when the specified properties changed. The properties can only be: 

* Transform related properties: ['x'][0], ['y'][1], ['scaleX'][2], ['scaleY'][3], ['rotation'][4], ['originX'][5], ['originY'][6]. For example:

      renderItem: function (params, api) {
          var coord = api.coord([api.value(0), api.value[1]);
          return {
              type: 'rect',
              x: coord[0],
              y: coord[1],
              shape: {
                  x: 0,
                  y: 0,
                  width: api.value(2),
                  height: 100
              },
              transition: ['x', 'y', 'width']
          }
      }
* Shortcut to transition all of the properties in ['shape'][7], ['style'][8], ['extra'][9]. For example:

      renderItem: function (params, api) {
          return {
              type: 'rect',
              shape: {
                  x: api.value(0),
                  y: api.value(1),
                  width: api.value(2),
                  height: api.value(3)
              },
              // Indicate that all props in `shape` will
              // have transition animation.
              transition: 'shape',
          };
      }


It is equivalent to:

      renderItem: function (params, api) {
          return {
              type: 'rect',
              shape: {
                  x: api.value(0),
                  y: api.value(1),
                  width: api.value(2),
                  height: api.value(3),
                  // This usage can only enable part of the
                  // properties transition.
                  transition: ['x', 'y', 'width', 'height']
              }
          };
      }

By default, ['x'][0] and ['y'][1] are transitioned. If you want to disable the default transition, just set it as: 

    transition: [] // Am empty array.


See this [example][10] please.

